        "id": "0aebaba2b9838fc5",
        "text": "Our world is shaped by the stories told and they are also fundamental to change processes. What makes a story powerful is not necessarily the facts themselves, but how the story creates meaning in the hearts and minds of the listeners. This means the main obstacle to convincing people of the need for change is often not linked to what they don’t yet know, but actually what they already do know. In other words, people’s existing mindsets, the assumptions and beliefs held, can act as narrative filters to prevent them from hearing social change messages."
      },
      "date": 1638060851637
