        "text": "The narrative of schooling is a relatively consistent and resilient story. Despite rhetoric about change, we unfortunately continue to deliver an industrial age model of learning. In the social construct of our schools, educators essentially maintain the system they know.  This is one in which the product (assignment, test, task) is always more important than the learning process."
